==English==
===Noun===
'''[[personal]] [[jurisdiction]]'''
# {{law}}: In the law of [[civil procedure]], the ability of a court to hear a case based on the authority granted to the court to hear that particular type of case.
#: The divorce court was overturned when it rendered a criminal conviction against a party, because it lacked the '''subject matter jurisdiction''' to hear a criminal case.

